OL,3,CScotland's controversial new hate
OL,4,Ccrime laws come into force
OL,6,FThe Hate Crime and Public Order
OL,7,F(Scotland) Act was passed by MSPs in
OL,8,F2021, consolidating existing hate
OL,9,Fcrime legislation and creating a new
OL,10,Foffence of stirring up hatred against
OL,11,Fprotected characteristics, although
OL,12,Fsex has been omitted in favour of a
OL,13,Fstandalone Bill designed to tackle
OL,14,Fmisogyny.
OL,16,FA stirring up offence on the basis of
OL,17,Frace has been on the statute book in
OL,18,FScotland since 1986.
